733317f-a.title: Street scenes - Newsstands.
733317f-a.text:
Street Scene--Manhattan: The news stand at the corner of
Lenox Avenue and W. 125th Street in Harlem.
January 1938
Alexander Alland
This is one of a series that appeared in the published volume "Portrait of N. Y." by Felix Reisenberg and Alex. Alland, IRGV.
NEG. 4307
733317f-a.folder: Lenox Avenue and 125th Street (West), Manhattan, N.Y.

715391f-b.text:
(1)
W. 125th Street, east fron Lenox Avenue. To the right is the Marion Building, at the S.W. corner of this point. The Harlem Branch of the Chatham Phenix National Bank is on the north side of this thoroughfare and east of the Avenue. In the far background is the Lee Building, located at the N.E. corner of Park Averue and W. 125th Street. The automobiles in the foreground obstruct a clear view of the N.Y.C.R.R. elevated tracks
and station at that point.
May 1928.
Geo. L. Balgue
(2)
The structures at the N.E. corner of Lenox Avenue and W. 125th Street. Note at the right the bank building occupied
at this date by the Manufacturers Trust Co.
July 28, 1932.
P.L. Sperr
